title: fanoutqa: Which currently sitting US Supreme Court Justices graduated from a top 14 law school? (8e62c5c69ce8c58d)

chat_history.content: Which currently sitting US Supreme Court Justices graduated from a top 14 law school?

The top 14 law schools in the United States are as follows:
1. Yale Law School
2. Stanford Law School
3. Harvard Law School
4. University of Chicago Law School
5. Columbia Law School
6. New York University School of Law
7. University of Pennsylvania Law School
8. University of Michigan Law School
9. University of Virginia School of Law
10. Duke University School of Law
11. Northwestern Pritzker School of Law
12. University of California, Berkeley School of Law
13. University of Texas School of Law
14. Cornell Law School

Here are the current Supreme Court Justices who graduated from the top 14 law schools:
- John G Roberts: Harvard Law School
- Clarence Thomas: Yale Law School
- Samuel A Alito Jr: Yale Law School
- Sonia Sotomayor: Yale Law School
- Brett M Kavanaugh: Yale Law School
- Amy Coney Barrett: Notre Dame Law School
